The MHD of Prague takes us on Wednesday for the first time with the chip
Wednesday, October 1, 2008, is written in the history of the Prague Transportation Company the date on which the first passengers enter the metro, tram and bus with an electronic bonus in their pockets instead of a paper note.
This can now be purchased by almost one hundred thousand people who own the Opencard chip card.
Passengers can buy the 30-day, 90-day bonus and the annual bonus (this will be valid as of 1 January 2009) and simultaneously load it on their chip card in the infocentres and positions of the transport company at the Metro stations, Muzeum, M'stek, Nádraží Holešovice, Anděl, Roztyly, Letňany, Kobylisy, Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
Bonuses can already be purchased on the Internet on the pages of the transport company, www.dpp.cz.
The service, up to the afternoon, was used by more than four hundred people.
Those who start using the internet as a form of trade, can definitely start to forget about the ticket sales posts at subway stations, where so far they had to queue regularly to get out a regular ticket.
The bonus is purchased on the Internet, and the Opencard card is reloaded to you in one of the thirteen branches of the Municipal Library.
"In these places there is at hand a window with trained staff that helps those interested in internet shopping and also with the recharging of the bonus purchased on your card," said the project spokesman Martin Opatrný.
Apart from the library, it will also be possible to reload the e-bony on the Opencard in the vending machines that are found in some subway halls.
How are these vending machines?
They are red, they remind us of a pick-up machine and the travelers will probably have already been fixed on them at the stations of the Roztyly Metro, Budějovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská.
"There are now five in the city but at the end of the year there should be eighty," Opatrný completed.
The bonus is controlled by the machine instead of the driver
Using the machine, which will start working tomorrow, is simple.
Just enter the Opencard chip card into it and the previously paid bonus will be loaded only on it.
The electronic bonds from tomorrow are valid not only in the capital but also in its surroundings.
In other words, in the circumvalition trains and bus lines from numbers 300 to 499 that mainly use the inhabitants of central Bohemia.
"In the trains attached to the integrated transport of Prague there are reviewers equipped with a reader card that will help confirm the validity of the time and the bonus area," explained the ticket control, Filip Drápal of the organization Ropid that sets the schedules for the collective transport of Prague.
Surrounding buses have their reader cards mounted on the driver's locker.
When entering it is necessary not only to show the card to the driver but also to accompany it with the Opencard at the location intended for it on the side of the Fund.
With this, the driver controls the validity of the bonus.
"If the passenger needs to verify the validity of the bonds there is nothing easier than asking the driver for this information," Drápal completed.
Passengers who do not travel on circumvalition buses and do not remember when they are finished the validity of the bonus can go to the vending machines where the cards are reloaded.
Here, on the machine screen, you will be presented with information on the validity of your document.
