"In the stamp the name of our company and the NIF appeared in the wrong place."
He added: In addition to the formal problems, he did not agree that according to the invoice a hundred people were accommodated, since they have only eleven rooms in which so many people do not belong.
In addition, meals were also included in the bill, while the restaurant has been out of operation for a long time.
Enthusiast invoice manufacturers were also not informed that the travel agency chosen in Budapest organizes exclusively trips abroad, so that in the cash payment bill they foolishly indicated as service a trip within Hungary, which did not coincide with the agency's billing practice.
Moreover - as was known during the investigation - VAT also included in the document, despite the fact that travel outside the European Union was tax-free.
Among other things, the VAT measure was also incorrect in the four documents issued by the Hotel Revfülöp Kft. for the Jobb Jövěért Foundation, since the services of that company were not loaded with 25 but only with 15 percent VAT, besides the hotel employees only extended invoices made by machine, however the invoice was manual.
In addition, the "shipper" made other mistakes as well, as in the case of a company in which they put on the invoice as an activity carried out the road transport to which - it was known during the investigations of the prosecutor's office - does not carry out the company founded as an investment consultant.
Also due to formal differences - inadequate invoice format, false stamp - it is known that the invoices issued for Együtt to Harmadik Évezredert Alapítvány, for XXI. Századi Kulturalis Egyesület and for Biztos Pont are false.
As in the case of Ravenna Bt. or the Kunfehertó Sports Camp, whose representatives refused to issue such invoices.
