Today, the European Summit for Equal Opportunities has been launched in Paris, and its host is France, who is also President-in-Office of the European Union this year.
Lívia Járóka, a Member of the European People's Party for Fidesz, in his message addressed to the plenary, as one of the main speakers of this professional meeting, called attention to segregation in education, because it is one of the most serious violations that plague Roma children and is also the greatest obstacle to the existence of their interests.
